# Antigravity & AI Assistant Rules

As an AI assistant (Antigravity) working on this repository, you must always adhere to the following workflow rules to ensure smooth collaboration:

## 1. Always work from the latest commit
- Before starting any task or proposing changes, you **must** fetch and pull the latest changes from the remote repository.
- Run `git fetch --all` followed by `git pull` (or checkout `main` and pull) to sync your local environment.

## 2. Always create a branch and open a Pull Request (PR)
- Do **not** commit or push changes directly to the `main` branch.
- Always create a new, descriptively named branch for any edits (e.g., `git checkout -b feature/some-feature` or `docs/update-info`).
- After completing the work, push the branch to the remote repository and create a Pull Request (using `gh pr create` if the GitHub CLI is available).
